  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, when configuring `quarkus-jacoco` extension on a project and running tests, the report title is defined as the name of the first`@QuarkusTest` class.\r\n\r\nIt'd be nice if the title is defined as the name of the current project (POM.project.name, which internally defaults to POM.project.artifactId), similar to what is defined for `jacoco-maven-plugin`.\r\n\r\nMore info:\r\n- https://www.eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/report-mojo.html#title\r\n- https://stackoverflow.com/questions/78577433/how-to-set-jacoco-report-name-with-quarkus/78580315\r\n\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nCurrent title:\r\n- $NameClass (QuarkusTest)\r\n\r\nTitle suggestions:\r\n- $POM.project.name (QuarkusTest)\r\n- $POM.project.name\r\n- quarkus.application.name\r\n- quarkus.application.name (QuarkusTest)",
